      • getKey

        protected abstract java.lang.Object getKey(IIdentifier freeIdentifier)
        return the key that this free identifier should be stored under. For instance, if this iidentifier is for an afferent object, the key would typically be the agent identifier portion.

        null should be returned if the identifier is not to be stored because it is of the wrong type or some such other reason.
